The paper discusses the weaknesses of the building block hypothesis in genetic algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of evolutionary computation and optimization (cs.NE). The paper also critiques the assumptions made by designers of "competent" genetic algorithms, which relates to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper uses mathematical arguments to support its claims, which suggests a focus on theoretical machine learning (cs.LG) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper analyzes the empirical record of genetic algorithms, which could be relevant to the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
